<p>Dereferencing a null pointer has undefined behavior, and it is particularly harmful if a reference is then bound to the result, because a reference
is assumed to refer to a valid object.</p>
<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>
<pre>
void doSomething(A&amp; a);
void f() {
  A* a = nullptr;
  // ...
  doSomething(*a); // Noncompliant
}
</pre>